Connect to a serial port:

$ minicom [-o] -b <baud rate> -D <serial device file>
 -o : do not perform initialization (useful for resuming an existing connection)

Example:

$ minicom -o -b 115200 -D /dev/ttyS0

<Ctrl-A> X to exit minicom

*****

Set up minicom to connect to a serial port automatically:

$ minicom -s
Serial port setup
   A - Serial Device : /dev/ttyUSB0 (or other appropriate device)
   E - Bps/Par/Bits : C, V, L, W for 9600 N81
   <Enter>
Exit
